EDS image of CDs exhibited the different atomic concentration percentages of the CDs (Fig. 3
                     ). The elements of C, N and O were calculated to be 72.23%, 6.04% and 21.73% respectively. The Elemental mapping graphs were provided in Fig. S2. The XRD pattern of the CDs was given and the diffraction peaks were situated at 26.51° (0,0,2), 44.88° (1,0.1), 51.61° (1,0,2) and 55.35° (0,0,4). Each signal was consistent with the Bragg peak of graphene (Reference code: 03-065-6212) (Fig. 4
                     a). This fact supported the achieved nanomaterial possessed a crystalline system.
